--## 2026-06-20 — Project Genesis and Foundation
--
--### Date
--2026-06-20
--
--### Source
--`#provenance: root/BUILD_LOG.md`
--
--### Decision
--Build a multi-agent orchestration platform on Hermes Agent, where specialized persona agents handle domain-specific tasks under a central Orchestrator supervisor.
--
--### Reasoning
--The user's initial brief: *"I want an agent that can research a company, analyze its finances, build something with that data, and present a report — all in one go. Not a chatbot that switches context. A system that orchestrates specialists."*
--
--Hermes Agent was chosen because:
--- Profile system provides natural isolation boundaries
--- Memory system supports persistent domain knowledge
--- Tool system allows granular permission control
--- Open-source and extensible
--
--Initial team: Financial Analyst, Research Analyst, Software Engineer (later renamed to Dev), Operations Manager, and the Orchestrator (root).
--
--### Changes Made
--- Installed and configured Hermes Agent
--- Created the 4 initial persona profiles
--- Set up the base `~/.hermes/profiles/` directory structure
--- Profiled tool access per-persona (whitelist in `config.yaml`) — fixing the default where every persona had access to every tool
--- Seeded core memory (`core/domain.md` and `core/constraints.md`) for all personas — they were starting as blank slates with no domain context
--
--### Lessons Learned
--- **Personas are not blank slates** — they're domain experts. Seed their memory before the first interaction.
--- **Default profile config was too permissive.** Every persona had access to every tool. The Research Analyst could execute system commands. Manual tool whitelisting per-profile fixed this.
--- **Memory was empty at first.** Personas started with no domain context, forcing re-explanation of each persona's job every session.
--
--### Follow-Up Actions
--- Monitor whether tool whitelisting needs further refinement as new tasks emerge
--- Evaluate if the 4-persona team is sufficient or if additional specialists are needed
