--## 2026-06-23 — Engineering Journal Implementation
--
--### Date
--2026-06-23
--
--### Source
--`#provenance: implementation`
--
--### Decision
--Establish a canonical Engineering Journal at `/root/docs/build-log.md` with standardized entry format, append-only policy, and a reusable Hermes skill for maintenance.
--
--### Reasoning
--Two build logs had grown in parallel — `/root/docs/BUILD_LOG.md` (308 lines, narrative/phase structure) and `/root/agent-env-selfhosted/docs/build-log.md` (164 lines, per-entry structure). Both contained engineering decisions, but:
--1. There was no single source of truth — maintainers had to check both files
--2. The formats were inconsistent — one used narrative sections, the other used per-entry structure
--3. There was no automated mechanism to ensure future entries follow a consistent pattern
--4. Provenance tracking was absent — entries couldn't be traced back to their source
--
--The Engineering Journal capability provides:
--- A canonical location (`/root/docs/build-log.md`) with a redirect from the old repo location
--- Standardized per-entry format with required fields (Date, Source, Decision, Reasoning, Changes Made, Lessons Learned, Follow-Up Actions)
--- Provenance tracking (`#provenance:`) so every entry is traceable to its origin
--- An append-only policy with explicit guardrails (no overwrites)
--- A reusable Hermes skill (`engineering-journal`) so any agent can maintain the journal consistently
--
--### Changes Made
--- Consolidated both build logs into `/root/docs/build-log.md` (this file)
--- Preserved all 8 entries from `/root/agent-env-selfhosted/docs/build-log.md` with `#provenance: repos/build-log.md`
--- Preserved all 5 phase narratives + 6 decision records from `/root/docs/BUILD_LOG.md` with `#provenance: root/BUILD_LOG.md`
--- Merged overlapping content (persona architecture decision from both sources)
--- Added standardized Source section with provenance tags to every entry
--- Added Changes Made and Follow-Up Actions sections (missing from some original entries)
--- Converted `/root/agent-env-selfhosted/docs/build-log.md` to a pointer/redirect
--- Created the `engineering-journal` Hermes skill at `~/.hermes/skills/documentation/engineering-journal/SKILL.md`
--- Preserved cross-cutting Lessons Learned, "What We'd Do Differently", and Build Timeline sections
--
--### Lessons Learned
--- **Document while it's fresh.** The original BUILD_LOG.md exists because decisions were forgotten two days after being made. The Engineering Journal formalizes this lesson into a repeatable pattern.
--- **Two parallel logs is worse than none.** Having two canonical sources means neither is canonical. Consolidation should happen as soon as a second source emerges.
--- **Provenance matters for historical accuracy.** Without tracking where information came from, migrated entries lose credibility and context.
--- The `#provenance:` tag pattern provides a lightweight audit trail without adding another tool or database.
--- The "Changes Made" and "Follow-Up Actions" sections were the most commonly missing fields in the original entries — the standardized format ensures they're never omitted going forward.
--
--### Follow-Up Actions
--- Update any references in ARCHITECTURE.md, CONFIGURATION.md, and other docs that point to the old repo build log location
--- Consider adding a CI check that validates new journal entries conform to the expected format
--- Review whether the `#provenance:` tag convention should be extended with timestamps or commit SHAs for entries that document their own modification
